[{"location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#Types","page":"API Reference","title":"Types","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.TRENDYDataset","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.TRENDYDataset","text":"TRENDYDataset\n\nRepresents a TRENDY model output dataset.\n\nFields\n\npath::String: Path to the NetCDF file\nmodel::String: Name of the TRENDY model\nsimulation::String: Simulation type (S0, S1, S2, S3)\nvariable::String: Variable name\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.ILAMBDataset","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.ILAMBDataset","text":"ILAMBDataset\n\nRepresents an ILAMB-compatible dataset.\n\nFields\n\npath::String: Path to the output NetCDF file\nvariable::String: Variable name in ILAMB convention\nunits::String: Units in CF convention\ntime_units::String: Time units (typically \"days since YYYY-MM-DD\")\ncalendar::String: Calendar type (typically \"noleap\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/#Conversion-Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Conversion Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.convert_to_ilamb","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.convert_to_ilamb","text":"convert_to_ilamb(dataset::TRENDYDataset; output_dir::String=\".\")\n\nConvert a TRENDY dataset to ILAMB format.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.verify_conversion","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.verify_conversion","text":"verify_conversion(dataset::TRENDYDataset, ilamb_dataset::ILAMBDataset)\n\nVerify the conversion between a TRENDY dataset and its ILAMB counterpart.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.compare_datasets","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.compare_datasets","text":"compare_datasets(ds1::Dataset, ds2::Dataset; name1::String=\"Dataset 1\", name2::String=\"Dataset 2\")\n\nCompare two NetCDF datasets and print their key properties.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Time-Handling","page":"API Reference","title":"Time Handling","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.convert_time_to_days","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.convert_time_to_days","text":"convert_time_to_days(years::Vector{Int}, reference_year::Int=1850)\n\nConvert years to days since a reference date.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.create_time_bounds","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.create_time_bounds","text":"create_time_bounds(years::Vector{Int}, reference_year::Int=1850)\n\nCreate time bounds array for ILAMB format. Returns an Array{Float64,2} with dimensions (n_times, 2) containing start and end days.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Utility-Functions","page":"API Reference","title":"Utility Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.standardize_units","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.standardize_units","text":"standardize_units(units::String)\n\nConvert TRENDY units to CF-compliant units.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.list_trendy_files","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.list_trendy_files","text":"list_trendy_files(root_dir::String, model::String, simulation::String)\n\nList all NetCDF files for a given TRENDY model and simulation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.extract_variable_name","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.extract_variable_name","text":"extract_variable_name(filepath::String)\n\nExtract the variable name from a TRENDY NetCDF filename.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#TRENDYtoILAMB.get_variable_metadata","page":"API Reference","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.get_variable_metadata","text":"get_variable_metadata(trendy_var::String)\n\nGet ILAMB-compatible metadata for a TRENDY variable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/#ILAMB-Format","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"The ILAMB (International Land Model Benchmarking) format is a standardized NetCDF format used for model benchmarking.","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/#File-Structure","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"File Structure","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"ILAMB files require:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"Spatial dimensions: lat, lon\nTemporal dimension: time\nTime bounds dimension: nb\nVariables:\nMain variable (e.g., cVeg)\nCoordinates (lat, lon, time)\ntime_bounds","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/#Units","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"Units","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"ILAMB requires CF-compliant units:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"Carbon pools: kg m-2\nFluxes: kg m-2 s-1\nTime: days since YYYY-MM-DD","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/#Example","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"Here's an example of an ILAMB-compatible file structure:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/ilamb_format/","page":"ILAMB Format","title":"ILAMB Format","text":"netcdf CLM5.0_S3_cVeg_ILAMB {\ndimensions:\n    lat = 192 ;\n    lon = 288 ;\n    time = 324 ;\n    nb = 2 ;\nvariables:\n    float cVeg(time, lat, lon) ;\n        cVeg:units = \"kg m-2\" ;\n        cVeg:long_name = \"Carbon in Vegetation\" ;\n    double lat(lat) ;\n        lat:units = \"degrees_north\" ;\n    double lon(lon) ;\n        lon:units = \"degrees_east\" ;\n    double time(time) ;\n        time:units = \"days since 1850-01-01\" ;\n        time:calendar = \"noleap\" ;\n        time:bounds = \"time_bounds\" ;\n    double time_bounds(time, nb) ;\n}","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/#TRENDY-Format","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"The TRENDY format refers to the standardized NetCDF file format used in the TRENDY (Trends in Net Land-Atmosphere Carbon Exchange) model intercomparison project.","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/#File-Structure","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"File Structure","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"TRENDY files typically contain:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"Spatial dimensions: lat, lon\nTemporal dimension: time (in years)\nVariables with attributes:\nMain variable (e.g., cVeg)\nCoordinates (lat, lon, time)","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/#Units","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"Units","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"TRENDY files often use the following units:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"Carbon pools: gC/m^2\nFluxes: gC/m^2/yr\nTime: years","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/#Example","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"Here's an example of a typical TRENDY file structure:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/trendy_format/","page":"TRENDY Format","title":"TRENDY Format","text":"netcdf CLM6.0_S3_cVeg {\ndimensions:\n    lat = 192 ;\n    lon = 288 ;\n    time = 324 ;\nvariables:\n    float cVeg(time, lat, lon) ;\n        cVeg:units = \"gC/m^2\" ;\n        cVeg:long_name = \"Carbon in Vegetation\" ;\n    double lat(lat) ;\n        lat:units = \"degrees_north\" ;\n    double lon(lon) ;\n        lon:units = \"degrees_east\" ;\n    int time(time) ;\n        time:units = \"yr\" ;\n}","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"To install TRENDYtoILAMB.jl, use Julia's package manager:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/braghiere/TRENDYtoILAMB.jl.git\")","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Basic-Usage","page":"Getting Started","title":"Basic Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"Here's a simple example of converting a TRENDY NetCDF file to ILAMB format:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"using TRENDYtoILAMB\n\n# Create a TRENDY dataset\ndataset = TRENDYDataset(\n    \"path/to/CLM5.0/S3/cVeg.nc\",\n    \"CLM5.0\",\n    \"S3\",\n    \"cVeg\"\n)\n\n# Convert to ILAMB format\nilamb_dataset = convert_to_ilamb(dataset, output_dir=\"output\")\n\n# Verify the conversion\nverify_conversion(dataset, ilamb_dataset)","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/#Supported-Variables","page":"Getting Started","title":"Supported Variables","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"Currently supported TRENDY variables include:","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"cVeg: Vegetation Carbon Content\ncSoil: Soil Carbon Content\ngpp: Gross Primary Production","category":"page"},{"location":"manual/getting_started/","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"Additional variables can be added by extending the VARIABLE_MAPPINGS dictionary in the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"#TRENDYtoILAMB.jl","page":"Home","title":"TRENDYtoILAMB.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for TRENDYtoILAMB.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"#Overview","page":"Home","title":"Overview","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"TRENDYtoILAMB.jl is a Julia package that converts TRENDY v13 model outputs into ILAMB-compatible format. It handles all necessary conversions including:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Time dimension standardization\nUnit conversions to CF convention\nMetadata enrichment\nVariable name mapping","category":"page"},{"location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","title":"Quick Start","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"```julia using TRENDYtoILAMB","category":"page"},{"location":"#Create-a-dataset-object","page":"Home","title":"Create a dataset object","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"dataset = TRENDYDataset(     \"/path/to/trendy/file.nc\",     \"CLM5.0\",     \"S3\",     \"cVeg\" )","category":"page"},{"location":"#Convert-to-ILAMB-format","page":"Home","title":"Convert to ILAMB format","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"ilambdataset = converttoilamb(dataset, outputdir=\"output\")","category":"page"}]
